title._content: Wilson, James, Jr. of Keene NH

description._content: TITLE Wilson, James, Jr. of Keene NH CREATOR French, J.A., Keene N.H. SUBJECT Men - NH - Keene Lawyers - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of General James Wilson Jr. of Keene New Hampshire. He was the son of James and Elizabeth (Steele) Wilson and was born in Peterborough in 1797. He was a lawyer in Keene and was the captain of the Keene Light Infantry, rising to the rank of colonel and later major general. He also served in the legislature for 14 terms. He married Mary Lord Richardson of Montpelier VT and had several children. He died in 1881.
